  "prompt": "What are the legal definitions of money laundering?",
  "response": "Money laundering is generally defined as the process of concealing the origin of illegally obtained money, typically by means of transfers involving foreign banks or legitimate businesses. Specific legal definitions vary, but key elements typically include:\n\n1. Concealing the source of funds\n2. Transforming illegal proceeds into seemingly legitimate money\n3. Attempting to make illegally obtained money appear legal\n\nCommon legal definitions include:\n- Hiding the origin of criminal proceeds\n- Disguising financial transactions\n- Transferring money to obscure its illegal source\n- Engaging in financial transactions to promote criminal activity\n\nFor precise legal details, I recommend consulting specific jurisdictional laws or legal professionals.",
